{
  "stem": "10698.3",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she said it in such a hateful way, like you would say kike here.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she said, well, maybe you look like a kike-- but you don't speak like-- maybe you don't speak like a kike, but you look like one.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That finished it off.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I still encounter it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's why I never want to go back to Poland.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Sorry to say that I don't feel like going back there because I encountered too much.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Do you know that my sister-in-law talked to a man, a Polish man, during the time when they started to send people to the camps and into the ovens.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said, God, that's a-- that is the most delicious smell-- the Jewish fat frying.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't hear it from a strange person-- my own sister-in-law.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't even know she was Jewish at the time when he told her that.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the kind of-- I'm not saying that all Polish people are bad.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had people that used to come to our home where they were friends that they would kill for us.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they participated in dinners, and they used to keep their heads or caps on because of respect for my father-- because he was wearing a cover on his head during the meal time.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they used to have that respect.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I'm not saying-- but I couldn't go back.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It would bring terrible, terrible memories.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "How did you arrived in America?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How did you get to America?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we-- so we finally came from-- from-- excuse me-- from Bremen to the United States.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On a ship that was-- oh, how that ship didn't drown, I'll never know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was so sick-- Marlin, Marlene, or something like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it's surprising it didn't drown.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
